```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
  width: 100vw;
}

.div {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
}
```

In this code:

*   `.container` is the parent element that contains the `.div` element.
*   `display: flex` enables flexbox layout for the parent element.
*   `justify-content: center` centers the child element horizontally.
*   `align-items: center` centers the child element vertically.
*   `height: 100vh` and `width: 100vw` set the height and width of the parent element to the full height and width of the viewport, respectively. This is necessary to create a container that can be centered.

